quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  23,78,And it is He who created your hearing and vision and hearts; how seldom are you grateful
  23,79,"And it is He who spread you over the earth, and to Him you will be gathered"
  23,80,"And It is He Who gives life and causes death, and to Him is due the alternation of night and day. Will you not then use your reason"
  23,81,"However, they are content to say what their ancestors said"
  23,82,"They said, \"When we die and become dust and bones, are we to be resurrected"
  23,83,"We have been promised this before, and so were our forefathers. These are just ancient legends"
  23,84,"Say, \"To whom belongs the earth and all that is in it, if you know"
  23,85,"They will say, \"To God.\" Say, \"Then will you not take heed"
  23,86,"Say, \"Who is Lord of the seven heavens and Lord of the Mighty Throne"
  23,87,"They will say, \"[They belong] to God.\" Say, \"Then will you not be mindful"
  23,88,"Say, \"In whose hand is the dominion over all things. Who protects, while none can protect against Him, if you happen to know"
  23,89,"They will say, \"[All belongs] to God.\" Say, \"Then how can you be so mislead"
  23,90,"In fact, We have sent them the Truth, but they lie"
  23,91,"God has not taken any son, nor has there ever been any other god but Him. [Had there been], then each god would have taken aside what it created, and sought to overcome the others. May God be exalted in His glory, far above what they ascribed to Him"
  23,92,"The Knower of all that is beyond human's perception, as well as all that can be witnessed by humans. May He be exalted above all whom they associate with Him"